race.comment: YOWERI (3) sat just off the speed as fav on debut when a respectable second over 1100m at Goulburn from the wide gate. Only has to hold that rating to win this. CASSEROUSSE (4) well-bred Exceed And Excel filly resuming. Raced keenly on debut when a fading sixth over 1000m at Kembla Grange on April 15. Looks primed after the two sharp trials. Gets her chance from the low gate. GATWICK (5) Ole Kirk filly from Invincible Express on debut for the Price & Kent yard. Looked strong in her latest trial when gapping her rivals over 801m at Warwick Farm. Big market watch and no shock to see her blow these away. COSMONAUT (2) three runs back have been even and gets one more chance today. Struck trouble at the start after being well supported late when a tiring seventh over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Each-way.
